# 📈 SPY Machine Learning Trading Dashboard

An end-to-end quantitative research project that combines time-series analysis, machine learning, technical indicators, explainable AI, and interactive visualization to investigate whether ML models can improve SPY ETF trading decisions.

The project develops a complete workflow:

- Market data acquisition
- Feature engineering
- Statistical modelling
- Deep learning experiments
- Machine learning classification
- Trading strategy construction
- Backtesting
- Risk analysis
- Explainability
- Interactive Streamlit dashboard


---

# 🚀 Project Overview

The main objective is to predict future SPY market direction and evaluate whether machine learning can provide a systematic trading advantage.

The final system combines:


XGBoost Classifier

SMA200 Market Regime Filter

Transaction Cost Adjusted Backtesting

Streamlit Interactive Dashboard


The final conclusion is that machine learning was more effective as a **risk-management overlay** rather than a standalone alpha-generation model.


