# 📊 Dataset

The project uses historical SPY ETF daily market data.

Data includes:

- Open
- High
- Low
- Close
- Volume


Additional technical features were generated to capture:

- Trend
- Momentum
- Volatility
- Mean reversion
- Volume behaviour


---

# 🧩 Feature Engineering

The final model uses engineered technical indicators.

## Trend Features

- SMA50
- SMA100
- SMA200
- SMA50/SMA200 relationship
- Distance from SMA200


## Momentum Features

- Rolling returns
- Momentum indicators


## Volatility Features

- Rolling volatility
- Bollinger Bands


## Volume Features

- Volume change
- Volume ratios


The objective was to capture different market states:

- Bull markets
- Bear markets
- High volatility periods
- Mean reversion opportunities


---

# 🤖 Models Tested


# 1. ARIMA

Purpose:

- Statistical return forecasting
- Time-series modelling


Result:

ARIMA struggled to predict future returns due to financial market noise and non-stationarity.



---

# 2. GARCH

Purpose:

- Volatility forecasting
- Risk estimation


Result:

GARCH provided useful volatility information but was not sufficient as a standalone trading strategy.



---

# 3. LSTM Neural Network

Architecture:


LSTM Layer
|
Dropout
|
Dense Output



Purpose:

Binary classification of future market direction.


Result:

The model suffered from prediction bias and limited generalization ability.



---

# 4. XGBoost Classifier

The final machine learning model.


Target:


Future 20-day return > 2%



Classification:


1 = Positive future return

0 = Otherwise



The model was selected because it provided:

- Better stability
- Feature importance interpretation
- Strong performance compared with previous approaches


---

# ⚙️ Hyperparameter Optimization

Final parameters:

```python
{
    "subsample": 0.8,
    "n_estimators": 800,
    "min_child_weight": 1,
    "max_depth": 4,
    "learning_rate": 0.05,
    "colsample_bytree": 1.0
}
📈 Model Performance

Classification results:

Accuracy: 51.6%

Precision: 48.7%

Recall: 54.3%

F1 Score: 51.4%

ROC AUC: 0.534

The model achieved a small predictive edge above random classification.

💹 Trading Strategy

The final strategy:

XGBoost Probability Prediction

+

SMA200 Market Regime Filter

+

Transaction Costs

Trading logic:

Generate probability of positive future return
Enter only when probability exceeds threshold
Trade only when SPY is above SMA200
Include transaction costs
📊 Backtesting Results
Buy & Hold SPY
Metric	Value
Annual Return	13.53%
Annual Volatility	17.63%
Sharpe Ratio	0.77
Maximum Drawdown	-24.50%
XGBoost + SMA200
Metric	Value
Annual Return	2.62%
Annual Volatility	8.28%
Sharpe Ratio	0.32
Maximum Drawdown	-16.88%
XGBoost + SMA200 + Transaction Costs
Metric	Value
Annual Return	1.50%
Annual Volatility	8.27%
Sharpe Ratio	0.18
Maximum Drawdown	-17.84%
🔍 Explainable AI (SHAP)

SHAP was used to understand model decisions.

Top influential features:

SMA200
SMA50/SMA200 relationship
Bollinger Lower Band
SMA100
Price distance from SMA200

Interpretation:

The model mainly learned:

Market trend
Long-term regime
Price deviation from historical averages

This confirms that the strategy behaves primarily as a trend/regime detection system.

🖥️ Streamlit Dashboard

The project includes an interactive Streamlit application.

Features:

✅ Live SPY data update

✅ Model probability prediction

✅ BUY / HOLD signal generation

✅ SMA200 market regime detection

✅ Price and trend charts

✅ Latest market data table

✅ SHAP feature importance visualization

✅ Adjustable prediction threshold

Run:

