📝 Final Conclusion

This project demonstrates a complete machine learning workflow applied to quantitative trading research.

The final model did not outperform passive SPY investment in absolute returns.

However, it successfully demonstrated that machine learning can:

Identify market regimes
Reduce portfolio volatility
Limit drawdowns
Provide interpretable trading signals

The main conclusion:

Machine learning models may provide greater value as risk-management systems rather than standalone return prediction engines.
